<figureCitation box="[337,440,1890,1915]" captionStart="FIGURE 59" captionStartId="98.[151,249,1953,1975]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,193,1932]" captionTargetId="figure@98.[151,1436,193,1932]" captionTargetPageId="98" captionText="FIGURE 59. Leucandra pilula sp.nov., SEM images of the spicules, a, giant triactines of the choanosome, b, cortical triactines, c, small triactines of the choanosome and subatrial region, d, tetractines of the atrial skeleton, e, fragment of trichoxea from the oscular rim." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1271435/files/figure.png" pageId="97" pageNumber="98">Figs 59d</figureCitation>
) of the atrial skeleton, sagittal, usually with unpaired actine shorter than paired actines, which are usually straight, occasionally slightly curved, unpaired actines 101– 
<emphasis box="[1042,1084,1926,1951]" italics="true" pageId="97" pageNumber="98">186</emphasis>
–271 
<date box="[1148,1197,1927,1951]" pageId="97" pageNumber="98" value="2014-10">x 14</date>
– 
<emphasis box="[1213,1262,1927,1951]" italics="true" pageId="97" pageNumber="98">19.4</emphasis>
–32 µm, paired actines 136– 
<emphasis box="[292,334,1963,1987]" italics="true" pageId="97" pageNumber="98">239</emphasis>
–380 
<date box="[397,431,1963,1987]" pageId="97" pageNumber="98">x 9</date>
– 
<emphasis box="[445,494,1963,1987]" italics="true" pageId="97" pageNumber="98">17.1</emphasis>
–32 µm, apical actines slightly curved, 45– 
<emphasis box="[977,1005,1963,1987]" italics="true" pageId="97" pageNumber="98">84</emphasis>
–130 
<date box="[1068,1102,1963,1987]" pageId="97" pageNumber="98">x 4</date>
– 
<emphasis box="[1117,1152,1963,1987]" italics="true" pageId="97" pageNumber="98">8.4</emphasis>
–11 µm.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="97.[151,1436,1710,2024]" box="[199,1361,1998,2024]" pageId="97" pageNumber="98">
Trichoxeas (
<figureCitation box="[338,432,1998,2023]" captionStart="FIGURE 59" captionStartId="98.[151,249,1953,1975]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,193,1932]" captionTargetId="figure@98.[151,1436,193,1932]" captionTargetPageId="98" captionText="FIGURE 59. Leucandra pilula sp.nov., SEM images of the spicules, a, giant triactines of the choanosome, b, cortical triactines, c, small triactines of the choanosome and subatrial region, d, tetractines of the atrial skeleton, e, fragment of trichoxea from the oscular rim." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1271435/files/figure.png" pageId="97" pageNumber="98">Fig. 59e</figureCitation>
) of the oscular region, not common, almost invariably broken, 100–300 
<date box="[1245,1308,1999,2023]" pageId="97" pageNumber="98">x 1–2</date>
µm.
</paragraph>
